reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars colorful and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: Standard size, third cut file folders. They are made of plastic rather than paper, giving them a lot more strength. They should last well. Good for those who need to carry their files around, not just leave them in the cabinet and use at your desk.Pretty colors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Plastic is so Much Neater than Cardboard
reviews.reviewText: I ordered the CreaNex Plastic File Folders because my paper files would get damaged every time I took them out of the file cabinet. The plastic feels a bit thinner than other plastic file folders that I used at the office and also thinner than the colored cardboard files that I have. It does seem to be more durable than the colored cardboard files. It resists bending and It bounces back when I try to bend the plastic. However, I did expect the files to be a bit thicker. My file cabinet does look much neater. I put the files I use most often in plastic folders because they get damaged the most. These plastic folders do have lines along the bottom so that you can expand them just as the cardboard ones do.The labels that came with the set are plastic also. This makes them easy to peel off and reset without tearing the label or folder if it is placed crookedly. I like this feature because the folders can be reused if a file is no longer needed. However, the labels are shorter than a popular name brand label which is paper (see photo). I really wish the labels were longer. I need more space on most of my file labels. There is plenty of room on the tab why did they shorten the label? For this reason and because they are a bit thinner than expected, I rated it 4 star.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Colorful, sturdy folders
reviews.reviewText: I try not to keep a lot of paper around the house, but a few things still end up needing filing. I wanted a few sturdy and also colorful folders so I can easily see which one to grab – like green for financial stuff, blue for receipts, etc. These folders are perfect for this! Very happy with them.The 12 pack gives you two folders of each color (6 colors total). Material is a thin flexible plastic that’s stronger than the typical manila folder. But they still have the standard 3 lines at the bottom where you can re-fold them to accommodate bigger or smaller contents. Also like classic manila folders, the tabs are 1/3 cut, meaning in differing places – left, center, right – so you can alternate them in a drawer to view the labels. They come with a total of 24 stick on labels in matching colors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Durable File Folders that Last as Long as You Need Them
reviews.reviewText: I love plastic file folders compared to the typical paper ones. I organize my financial papers, my vacation plans, my medical info, and so on, and I used to use regular paper file folders. They fray and the tabs get bent over. These plastic ones are long lasting, and the tabs hold their structure so you can easily find the folder you are looking for. These folders come in nice cheerful colors that help you quickly identify the one you are needing. Labels are included to affix to the tabs. These file folders almost make organizing your papers fun!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A wonderful replacement for well-worn heavy paper file folders
reviews.reviewText: These plastic file folders are exactly the same size as your everyday heavy paper file folders. They also have 3 fold lines across the bottom of one side that will enable me to expand the folders to hold files up to nearly 1" thick - that's a lot of pages. The best thing is that these are going to last forever and can be reused just by changing the label - I don't expect I'll ever have to replace them. I'll just need a few more to accommodate the rest of my files.
